===Etymology===
Old English ''fām''
===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg-both}}

# A substance composed of a large collection of [[bubbles]] or their solidified remains.
#:''He doesn't like so much '''foam''' in his beer.''
#:''A '''foam''' mat can soften a hard seat.''

